hopobject.body: We used to work together pharm-bay.com scam Secrecy and rigidity run deep in the Muslim Brotherhood, both reflecting a means of survival and suggesting why today's Muslim Brotherhood was as ill-suited for governing a nation successfully as it was adept at guiding an opposition. "Listen and obey" is a guiding principle for Muslim Brotherhood members, highlighting a leadership style that is inconsistent with Egypt's powerful, prevailing demographics. Half of all Egyptians are under the age of 25; this cohort is enervated, technologically well-connected and desperate for opportunities too long denied.
